text.__SUMMARY__:
Chamaelaucium confertiflorum is a member of the family Myrtaceae endemic to Western Australia.The slender and erect shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1.0 metre (1 to 3 ft). It blooms between October and December producing white flowers.Found in the Great Southern region of Western Australia where it grows in sandy or peaty soils.
